default7.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultYes, valuable lessons can be learned from the experiences of other countries
default 
default(Nijnik and Bizikova, 2008). e.g.
default a study analysing the cases  of Germany, Finland, the United Kingdom, the United States and Canada shows that these ‘early adapters’ (Bizikova et al., 2012) have an improved regional and national understanding of climatic impacts, and of the risks to agriculture before the initiation of the planning process. 
default7.1.1.
default 
defaultT
defaulthe interplay between bottom-up and top-down initiatives
default w
defaultas crucial in the development of adaptation strategies. The former has provided rich and robust participation in designing, implementing and monitoring adaptations, while the latter was important for prioritizing and legitimizing the development of strategy. It also provided access to high-level decision-makers and funding. 
