defaultNESEMPdefault: The ongoing North East Scotland energy monitoring project (NESEMP) is examining the relationship between different types of energy feedback and psycho-social measures including individual environmental attitudes, household characteristics, and everyday behaviours. As part of this on-going project, several hundred households are being monitored and the electricity usage is recorded every five minutes using CurrentCost monitors. (Craig, T., Galan-Diaz, C., Heslop, S., Polhill, J.: The North East Scotland Energy Monitoring Project (NESEMP). In: Workshop on Climate Change and Carbon Management. The James Hutton Institute (March 2012).
